quest_title:
The \(_{92} \mathrm{U}^{238}\) nucleus decays according to

\(_{92} \mathrm{U}^{238} \rightarrow _{90}\mathrm{Th}^{234}+_{2} \mathrm{He}^{4}\)

determine K.E. of emitted \(\alpha\) -particle if

\(_{92} \mathrm{U}^{238}=3.8539 \times 10^{-25} \mathrm{kg}\)
\(\mathrm{Th}^{234}=3.78737 \times 10^{-25} \mathrm{kg}\) and
\(_{2} \mathrm{He}^{4}=6.64807 \times 10^{-27} \mathrm{kg}\)
explanation_txt:
\(_{92} \mathrm{U}^{238} \longrightarrow _{90}\mathrm{Th}^{234}+_{2} \mathrm{He}^{4}\)
\(\Delta \mathrm{m}=_{92} \mathrm{U}^{238}-\left(_{90} \mathrm{Th}^{234}+_2 \mathrm{He}^{4}\right)\)
\(=3.8539 \times 10^{-5}-\left(3.78737 \times 10^{25}+6.64807 \times 10^{27}\right)\)
\(=4.93 \times 10^{-30} \mathrm{kg}\)
\(\mathrm{E}_{\mathrm{T}}=\Delta \mathrm{mc}^{2}\)
\(=4.93 \times 10^{30} \times\left(3 \times 10^{8}\right)^{2}\)
\(=4.437 \times 10^{-13} \mathrm{J}\)
Here, \(\cfrac{\mathrm{KE}_{\mathrm{Th}}}{\mathrm{KE}_{\alpha}}=\cfrac{\mathrm{m}_{\alpha}}{\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{Th}}}\)
or, \(\cfrac{\mathrm{KE}_{\mathrm{Th}}+\mathrm{KE}_{\alpha}}{\mathrm{KE}_{\alpha}}=\cfrac{\mathrm{m}_{\alpha}+\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{Th}}}{\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{Th}}}\)
or, \(\cfrac{\mathrm{KE}_{\alpha}}{\mathrm{E}_{\mathrm{T}}}=\cfrac{\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{Th}}}{\mathrm{m}_{\alpha}+\mathrm{m}_{\mathrm{Th}}}\)
\(\begin{aligned} \text { or, } \mathrm{KE}_{\alpha} &=\left(\cfrac{3.78737 \times 10^{-25}}{6.64807 \times 10^{27}+3.78737 \times 10^{-25}}\right) \times 4.437 \times 10^{-13}\\\ &=4.35 \times 10^{-13} \mathrm{J} \end{aligned}\)
